    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1880-04-22T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1880-04-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="614" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d614">
                <head>No. 614.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Heap</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Evarts</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Constantinople</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1880-04-22">
                            <hi rend="italic">April</hi> 22, 1880</date>.
                                (Received May 10.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 13.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: There is good authority for stating that
                            telegraphic dispatches were sent by the ministry of foreign affairs on
                            the 20th instant to the Ottoman ministers at Washington, Stockholm, and
                            Brussels to notify them that those legations were discontinued.</p>
                <p>These measures have been dictated by the necessities of the treasury.</p>
                <p>I have, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>G. H. HEAP,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Chargé d’Affaires ad
                                    interim.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
